document: <sentence id="s1" text="Three subcardiac muscle tissue developments, li>PTPN11- , positive regulation of endothelial cell proliferation-, and li>positive regulation of protein phosphorylation-mutated JMML, are characterized by heterozygous somatic gain-of-function mutations in non syndromic children, while two subcardiac muscle tissue developments, JMML in neurofibromatosis type 1 and in JMML in children with ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process syndrome, are characterized by germ line RAS disease and acquired biallelic inactivation of the respective tumor suppressor genes in hematopoietic cells.">
